<title type="html"><![CDATA[3/2(Thu)Earthquake in Syria and Turkey／8-year-old Indian Diamond Heiress Who Became a Nun (Host: Louie)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=705&amp;p=733#p733"><![CDATA[
3/2(Thu)Earthquake in Syria and Turkey／8-year-old Indian Diamond Heiress Who Became a Nun (Host: Louie)<br /><br />We will hold an on-site meeting only.<br />摩斯漢堡明曜店(每人低消 :60元)<br />台北市仁愛路4段151巷37號地下室.<br />MRT忠孝敦化站3號出口 , 明曜百貨後方第二個巷子口<br /><br /><br />Agenda<br />7:00-7:30 pm ：opening ＆free talk<br />7:30-8:00 pm: session I, the first topic, subgroup discussion<br />8:00-8:30 pm: session 2, the second topic ,subgroup discussion.<br />8:30-9:00 table topic<br /><br /><br />--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br /><br /><br />Session I : Millions Displaced in Turkey and Syria after Earthquake<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/feb/12/what-shall-we-do-millions-displaced-in-turkey-and-syria-after-earthquake">https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/ ... earthquake</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Question<br />1.What is your experience in earthquakes? What did you do then?<br />2.Do you always get a survival pack prepared just in case of serious quakes? What are normally required in a survival pack?<br />3.It’s hard to imagine being displaced after a disaster. What will you most likely do if that happens to you and makes you homeless?<br />4.Any movie about earthquakes you’ve ever watched? Please introduce it.<br />----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br /><br /><br />Session II: 8-year-old Indian Diamond Heiress Who Became a Nun<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-64327940">https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-64327940</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Question<br /><br />1. Do you believe a child or teenager can decide for his/her own life? Why?<br />2. Some religion hold it sacred to “baptize” a kid even infant at very young age. Do you agree with that?<br />3. What will you do in case your kids show strong interest in spiritual life and even about to renounce from the mundane world?<br />4. Sometimes what is allowed in religious world is not allowed in legal world (and vice versa). For example free speech against some religion may be considered as blasphemy. How should we show our respect to a religion or even to atheists?<br /><br /><br />P.S.<br />1.參加三次(含實體及線上會議)後，只要繳交1,000元(學生500元)，即可成為ROYAL終身會員!<br />2.請帶著開放的心與熱情來參加全英文會話聚會!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38674">Louie Wang</a> — Fri Feb 24, 2023 8:22 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
